text:
- good location;
- room noisy; smelly; needs renovation; super small; the wind can enter through the window;
- when you arrive there they charge you extra fees even when all the taxes are included;
- in the restaurant they add to the bill the tipo they want you cannot choose who you want to give;
- fees of 5€/luggage  
- 1 day without electricity on the sockets and zero compensation 
- towels from the floor were not changed even when you put on the ground.

Small room with double bed.  Small T.V in the room and a safe located in the cupboard.  Good shower with plenty of hot water.  Room maids were very helpful. Good location. Small breakfast deli in the lobby near Tic Tock diner entrance called The Butcher and Banker. Which had tea/coffee and a small selection of breakfast pastries available to buy.
Negatives;
We found the front desk staff to be quite aggressive.  Our luggage was not brought up to our room, we had to fetch it ourselves. The woman on the Concierge Desk was only interested in getting us to sign up for some kind of hotel sales at another hotel, rather than give us the information we were asking for!
